\begin_layout Section*
Motivation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In today's robotics still simple tasks require sophisticated and complex
 approaches to solve them.
 At least there are some robot platforms that provide highler level task
 solving capabilities 
\begin_inset Note Note
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Reference
\end_layout

\end_inset

 but they are mostly optimized for a special task and limited to a certain
 environment.
 Thus basically the problem to approach common tasks with robots remains.
 Typical tasks for a mobile robot require at least some sensors like a stereo
 vision camera, a robot arm or even a hand.
 To interconnect that sensors in software in a meaningful way is not a trivial
 assignment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To conclude even simple tasks like 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

grip that trash there
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

open that door
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 of 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

find the pink one
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 can be assumed to be complex tasks.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Complex tasks can be solved be a few sphisticated robots or multiple relative
 simple robots which coordinate themselves.
 As described in the next section there a important advantages of the latter
 category.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section*
Goal
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the following subsections the advantages of a distributed multi-robot
 platform will be introduced.
 This work is about to provide such a platform to the user.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
Task Flexibility
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "sub:Flexibility"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Tasks for robots can be very manigfold.
 To address this the robot platform shall be capable of accepting versatile
 tasks and manage a dynamical and heterogenous group of robots to solve
 them.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
Scalability
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The platform shall be enbabled to be on-the-fly extendable by new robots
 as well as to overcome malfunction.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
Cost
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This work assumes that a group of heterogenous and smaller robots is mid-
 to long-term cheaper in maintenance than a few highly specialised ones.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
Platform Flexibility
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The later support for different robot and agent platforms shall be prepared.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
Scenarios
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The scenarios are partly taken from 
